&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Construction Project Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the planning, execution, and close-out of facility construction projects supporting Colossal Biosciences’ de-extinction and conservation science mission. This role will serve as the primary owner’s representative on complex construction efforts — including specialized life sciences and animal facility builds — ensuring projects are delivered on time, within budget, and to the highest quality standards. The Senior Construction Project Manager will manage general contractors, design teams, and key stakeholders, acting as the central point of accountability from project inception through facility activation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary owner’s representative for construction projects, including specialized facilities such as avian, laboratory, and life sciences spaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all phases of the project lifecycle: programming and design coordination, construction oversight, close-out, commissioning, and facility activation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and oversee general contractors, architects, engineers, IT/AV/security vendors, and equipment suppliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate project scope, budget, and schedule at project initiation; monitor and report performance throughout the project lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review contractor schedules, submittals, shop drawings, and RFIs to ensure compliance with contract documents, drawings, and specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular jobsite visits and provide weekly construction review status reports and monthly progress updates to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Receive, review, and process change order requests; evaluate unit prices, time and material charges, and obtain appropriate client approvals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate procurement of long-lead items and equipment to align with project schedule and commissioning milestones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all legally required permits, licenses, and certificates in coordination with local municipal authorities, governmental agencies, and utility companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee punch list management, warranty coordination, and creation of owner’s manuals and training requirements to facility management teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage lab and facility activation and commissioning processes; coordinate functional performance testing with landlords and contractors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain comprehensive project budgets, tracking expenditures against financial forecasts and reporting variances to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare detailed project reports documenting phases, milestones, risks, issues, and final outcomes for executive stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with vendors, contractors, and internal teams across scientific, operations, and finance functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development of standard operating procedures, project management templates, RFP documents, budget trackers, and cost metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills and Abilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience as an owner’s representative or construction project manager on commercial, life sciences, laboratory, or specialty facility projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong command of all construction project phases: design coordination, construction administration, close-out, and commissioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage general contractors, and multidisciplinary design teams simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in project scope, schedule, and cost management with experience overseeing multi-million-dollar project budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in reviewing construction documents, contracts, change orders, and pay applications.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Colossal is a breakthrough bioscience and genetic engineering company that builds radical new technologies to advance the field of genomics. Colossal creates disruptive technologies for extinct species restoration, critically endangered species protection/conservation and the repopulation of critical ecosystems that support the continuation of life on Earth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested in joining us in a full-time role but there are no jobs posted that match your background and/or interest? Apply here to join our Colossal Talent Community!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some things to know:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;After the application confirmation email gets to you, we will only reach out if/when a new role opens up that aligns to your qualifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our positions are currently located on-site in Dallas, TX.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All applicants must be authorized to work in the United States to be eligible for hire.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The majority of our roles are in the biological sciences and engineering. We also hire in animal care as well as all corporate functions such as finance, human resources, information technology, legal, marketing, and operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the meantime, keep an eye on our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.colossal.com/careers&quot;&gt;Careers Website&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for new job opportunities!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn more about what we do and why we do it at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://colossal.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://colossal.com/&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about the de-extinction of the Woolly Mammoth here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://colossal.com/mammoth/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://colossal.com/mammoth/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about the de-extinction of the Thylacine (Tasmanian Tiger) here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://colossal.com/thylacine/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://colossal.com/thylacine/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about the de-extinction of the Dodo Bird here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://colossal.com/dodo/&quot;&gt;https://colossal.com/dodo/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about the de-extinction of the Dire Wolf here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://colossal.com/direwolf/&quot;&gt;https://colossal.com/direwolf/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about the exciting science happening in our labs here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://colossal.com/technology/&quot;&gt;https://colossal.com/technology/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn about our amazing conservation work here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://colossal.com/conservation/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://colossal.com/conservation/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check out our page on de-extinction here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://colossal.com/de-extinction/&quot;&gt;https://colossal.com/de-extinction/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Colossal Offers Full-Time Employees:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
